### What was wrong?
Viper wasn't supported :tongue: 


### How was it fixed?

Added the necessary code in ViperBackend. Currently you have to specify the backend as part of your project.json as follows:

```json
{
    "version": "7",
    "compilation": {
        "contracts_source_dirs": ["./contracts"],
        "import_remappings": [],
        "backend": {
            "class": "populus.compilation.backends.ViperBackend"
        }
    }
}
```

Then you can add .v.py file in contracts path as follows (this replicates default init Greeter contract):
```python
cat contracts/Greeter.v.py 
greeting: bytes <= 20

@public
def __init__():
    self.greeting = "Hello"

@public
def setGreeting(x: bytes <= 20):
    self.greeting = x

@public
def greet() -> bytes <= 40:
    return self.greeting

```

To test you can simply install viper (

